1
00:00:00,120 --> 00:00:05,520
If you stay, I’ll teach you the best swing 
trading strategies that work on any market,  

2
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:08,360
whether it’s Forex, stocks or crypto.
 
Monthly pivot 

3
00:00:08,360 --> 00:00:14,000
The first strategy involves the monthly pivots, 
which are the secret weapon of swing trading. 

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:18,760
They are based on the previous month's 
high, low, and close, and will give you  

5
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:24,720
a rough idea of where the market might find 
support & resistance in the coming weeks.
  

6
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:30,120
Monthly pivots are like the big boss of 
support and resistance levels. They carry  

7
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:35,520
a lot more weight than your average daily pivot.
That’s because they represent a whole month's  

8
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:39,160
worth of price action, not 
just a snapshot in time. 
  

9
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:43,800
This levels acts as a magnet, attracting 
the price on higher time frames. 

10
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:49,040
The big market players are watching these levels, 
and when the price interacts with a monthly pivot,  

11
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:54,760
it can trigger some serious fireworks.
 
The more time the price spends above the pivot,  

12
00:00:54,760 --> 00:01:00,720
the more reliable it becomes as a support level.
And, the more time the price spends below  

13
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:05,680
the pivot, the more reliable it 
becomes as a resistance level.
  

14
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:12,080
The strategy here is to look for confluences 
between the monthly pivot and supply/demand areas. 

15
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:17,680
It doesn't happen every day, but when it 
does, it can be a sign of something special!
  

16
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:22,200
Let's say you're looking at a chart and you 
notice that the price is approaching a key  

17
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:28,920
demand area that lines up with a monthly pivot.
That's a confluence perfect for a swing trade. 
  

18
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:34,080
If the price bounces off that area, it could 
be the start of a beautiful uptrend that you  

19
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:39,120
can ride for weeks or even months.
 
On the flip side, if you see the  

20
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:44,520
price approaching a major supply area 
that coincides with the monthly pivot,  

21
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:48,680
it could be a sign that the buyers 
are about to run out of steam. 
  

22
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:55,480
If the price gets rejected at that level, it might 
be time to start hunting for short opportunities.
 

23
00:01:55,480 --> 00:02:00,480
Of course, these confluences between 
monthly pivots and supply/demand areas  

24
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:05,840
aren't the only thing you should be looking for.
You'll also want to keep an eye on candlestick  

25
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:12,400
patterns, like pin bars and engulfing bars.
When you find a candlestick with a long wick,  

26
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:16,560
rejecting the monthly pivot, 
that’s a really good signal.
  

27
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:21,440
Now, what if the price blows right 
through the monthly pivot. It will happen,  

28
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:25,760
because no level is unbreakable, and 
sometimes the market will just keep  

29
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:31,680
moving with momentum, even on higher time frames.
 
Even if the price does break through the monthly  

30
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:38,000
pivot, it can still give you valuable information 
about the strength and direction of the trend. 

31
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:42,720
For example, if the price breaks above 
the monthly pivot, it could be a sign  

32
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:48,080
that the buyers are in control and that 
the trend has momentum to continue. 

33
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:52,680
The pivot that once acted as 
resistance now becomes a new support,  

34
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:58,560
helping the price to reach new heights!
 
On the other hand, if the price breaks below the  

35
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:05,040
monthly pivot and starts to accelerate, it might 
be time to start looking for short opportunities. 

36
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:09,920
The sellers have taken control of the market, 
and they'll do everything in their power to  

37
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:16,040
keep the price from rising back above the pivot.
Now the pivot has become a resistance, pushing the  

38
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:19,280
price down when it tries to break through.
 
 
3 BB

39
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:24,280
The second swing trading strategy 
involves using Bollinger Bands indicator. 

40
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:29,440
It might look a bit strange at first, because 
you're going to use three Bollinger Bands.
  

41
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:35,400
First add Bollinger Band with a Period 
of 50 and a Standard Deviation of 1.
  

42
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:41,520
Then add the Second Bollinger Band with a 
Period of 50 and a Standard Deviation of 2.
  

43
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:47,480
The Third Bollinger Band will have a Period 
of 50 and a Standard Deviation of 3.
 
  

44
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:54,320
With this setup, the trend is pretty clear to see.
Let’s consider an uptrend, with different stages. 

45
00:03:54,320 --> 00:04:01,200
When price is between the middle line, the 50 E 
MA, and the first band, that's a weak uptrend.
  

46
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:07,320
In this area, there's no strong momentum. 
Price is likely to bounce around in a range  

47
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:12,760
and might even dip below the middle line.
You can buy in this area, but only if you  

48
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:17,280
have other factors lining up. 
 
When price is between the first  

49
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:23,040
and second Bollinger Bands above the 
50 E MA, that's a strong uptrend. 

50
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:26,800
There's a better chance that 
price will keep going up.
  

51
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:32,680
As long as candles keep closing in this buy 
zone, the odds are in favor of holding current  

52
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:38,880
long positions or even opening new ones.
 
When price is between the second and third  

53
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:43,800
Bollinger Bands, above the middle 
line, that's a very strong uptrend. 

54
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:49,440
Price is stretched and I would avoid 
buying if price goes outside the bands.
  

55
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:54,800
Looking for overlaps of major support and 
resistance levels with Bollinger Bands is  

56
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:59,760
a great way to find swing trading setups.
These confluence areas tend to attract  

57
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:05,120
more buyers or sellers, leading to 
a reversal or a trend continuation. 

58
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:09,840
With this confluence, you're basically 
finding pullbacks in a strong trend.
  

59
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:15,360
When a market is in an uptrend (meaning price is 
above the middle Bollinger Band) and you find a  

60
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:21,880
confluence between a recent support or resistance 
level and one of the standard deviation bands,  

61
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:27,920
you can trade a bounce off that area.
 
On the flip side, when price is in a downtrend  

62
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:33,920
(below the middle band) and a recent support or 
resistance lines up with one of the lower bands,  

63
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:40,600
a decent pullback trade might be setting up.
 
Looking at this chart, it's obvious how much price  

64
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:47,400
respects the bands. Even when price was below the 
middle band, it found support at the lower bands.

65
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:53,360
And here, price broke above the middle band and 
also broke this resistance level, which could  

66
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:57,720
potentially now act as support. 
 
Here's our value area. 

67
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:03,240
The first band above the middle line and 
this level are lining up at the same point. 

68
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:09,600
This is a solid trend continuation opportunity.
 
Finding profit targets is very easy. You just  

69
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:13,960
aim for the next bands. The first 
take profit is at the second band,  

70
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:19,920
and the next target is the last band.
 
As a tip, always expect momentum to slow  

71
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:25,000
down when price reaches the next set of 
bands. That’s why it’s best to take some  

72
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,960
of your profits at these levels.
 
 
21 EMA channel at round numbers

73
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:33,160
The third swing trading strategy involves 
taking advantage of round numbers. And we’ll  

74
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:39,360
confirm the signals using 2 moving averages.
 
First, you plot two 50-period Exponential Moving  

75
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:47,000
Averages on your chart - one applied to the 
high price and the other to the low price. 
  

76
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:51,320
These lines will act like dynamic 
support and resistance levels.
  

77
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:56,920
The beauty of this channel lies in its simplicity.
When the price is trading above the channel, it's  

78
00:06:56,920 --> 00:07:03,600
a bullish signal, suggesting that the trend is up, 
and it's time to look for buying opportunities. 

79
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:08,960
When the price is below the channel, it's a 
bearish signal, indicating that the trend is  

80
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:14,160
down and it's time to consider selling.
 
When you combine this channel with the  

81
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:19,880
psychological significance of round numbers, 
you've got a really good swing trading strategy. 

82
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:26,520
Round numbers are those big, juicy price 
levels that end in double or triple zeros. 
  

83
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:32,840
These levels hold a special place in the minds of 
traders, often acting as key areas of interest. 

84
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:39,040
Round numbers are not just some arbitrary figures 
on a chart. They are psychological anchors and  

85
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:42,800
catalysts for market movements.
 
There's a deep psychological  

86
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:47,800
aspect to round numbers that makes them so 
powerful. We are naturally drawn to whole numbers,  

87
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:53,320
and we tend to assign more significance to them.
When the price approaches a round number,  

88
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:59,480
it's like a magnet, drawing in all sorts of 
attention and potential trading activity.
  

89
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:03,000
Here’s how you find signals.
First, you look at the moving  

90
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:08,080
average channel to determine whether the 
market is in an uptrend or a downtrend. 

91
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:13,120
Then you locate the closest round numbers 
that the price is approaching. This will  

92
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:17,080
be your key levels to watch.
 
If the price is in an uptrend,  

93
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:21,880
supported by the moving averages, and 
approaching a round number from below,  

94
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:28,040
you look to buy a breakout ABOVE the level. 
 
If the price is in a downtrend and approaching  

95
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:35,200
a round number from above, you look to sell 
a breakout BELOW the psychological level.
 
  

96
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:40,560
This channel acts a as a trampoline. When 
the price breaks it and then returns to hit  

97
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:47,560
the upper or lower EMA, it's like a test bounce.
If the channel holds and the price bounces off it,  

98
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:51,080
it's a confirmation that the 
channel is indeed valid.
  

99
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:55,000
This first bounce is crucial because 
it validates the channel as a  

100
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:00,360
significant level of support or resistance.
When you have an initial bounce, be ready to  

101
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:06,680
trade the next bounces, near round numbers.
 
So very important: an initial rejection of  

102
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:10,760
the channel is a good sign that the 
channel is holding firm and that the  

103
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:17,240
price is likely to respect it in the future.
This second or third bounce is like a green light,  

104
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:21,820
signaling that it's time to pay attention 
and prepare for a potential trade.
  

105
00:09:21,820 --> 00:09:26,240
Here another crucial tip. When the 
price is caught inside the channel  

106
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:32,760
for more than three candles, and is located 
near a round number, avoid taking a trade. 

107
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:38,560
In this situation, the market is experiencing 
consolidation. It's a time of uncertainty,  

108
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:43,680
where the price is searching for 
direction, inside the 2 EMAs. 
  

109
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:47,800
Trying to trade during this period 
is like trying to predict the outcome  

110
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:52,960
of a coin toss, it's like a gamble.
So, when the price is trapped inside  

111
00:09:52,960 --> 00:10:00,640
the channel for more than three candles, simply 
stay on the sidelines and wait for clarity. 
  

112
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:05,560
You want to see an immediate reaction around 
the channel, a quick rejection of the area,  

113
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:08,360
like in this example.
Now, if you want to  

114
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:21,600
learn other trading techniques, you 
definitely must watch our next videos.

